19.	If an ArrayList contains duplicate objects and remove() 
    method is invoked on the same object, will it remove the duplicates?
    
    No, if an ArrayList contains duplicate objects and you use the remove() method 
    on one occurrence of the object, it will only remove the first occurrence of that object. 
****************************************************************************************
20.	How to reverse an ArrayList in Java?

   To reverse an ArrayList in Java, you can use the Collections.reverse() method 
   from the java.util package. This method reverses the order of elements in the specified list.


